        <briefdescription>
<para>Is <computeroutput>name</computeroutput> a valid register block name? </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If this returns 1, then <ref refid="group__devicetree-reg-prop_1gaeb5863e878bbd3a362e17616403da692" kindref="member">DT_REG_ADDR_BY_NAME(node_id, name)</ref> or <ref refid="group__devicetree-reg-prop_1ga042988feb27e58989baa7abb4930409e" kindref="member">DT_REG_SIZE_BY_NAME(node_id, name)</ref> are valid. If it returns 0, it is an error to use those macros with name <computeroutput>name</computeroutput>. <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>node_id</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>node identifier </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>name</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>name to check </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>1 if <computeroutput>name</computeroutput> is a valid register block name, 0 otherwise. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
